A rather hidden rooftop bar located in the heart of the Loop. Great spot for taking an out-of-town friend to a place that's not too popular yet still have stunning views.  Cerise Rooftop is located on top of the Virgin Hotel near the river in Chicago. It's relatively hidden location makes for a less crowded area yet with still good views. The music is fantastically good. Expect more of a chill, hip EDM scene.  I did not eat anything while here. I did order drinks on many occasions. Drinks are on the pricier side and options are a bit limited. Basic cocktails are available but this place isn't known for its cocktails. The drinks are best enjoyed while enjoying the view and chatting with a friend.  The service is great. I've not yet had any issues with them tending to me. That's saying a lot as some rooftop bars I've been to tend to be overwhelmed or lack good service.  One small complaint I do have is that the restroom is inconveniently located on the floor below the rooftop bar. Though not a long flight of stairs, it can be a bit of a hassle to get down there. If I could make one change to this place, it would be to move the restrooms up to the floor this bar is on.  4/5. A bit on the pricier side but a great recommendation for anyone looking for a rooftop bar in downtown Chicago.

Lovely rooftop bar. Great view! Since it is a little off the beaten path there were available tables on a busy Sunday afternoon. You can see the river and the Trump tower from a little distance and the cupolas of the Jeweler’s building up close. Not too many specialty cocktails listed but the “RBG Baby” was pretty good. I also liked the “Summer Tonic” but the whole peppercorns made it problematic to drink except using the tiny straws. Still, for the view I would recommend this place for sure. One random thing is that the men’s and women’s restrooms share sinks...which feels odd.
